2 functions must be given:
one for the DILATATION and one for the REFERENCE TEMPERATURE.
These 2 functions have the same parameters

The order of 7 parameters of the USER's function
HEAT DILATATION or REFERENCE TEMPERATURE
at time TEMPS, at point X,Y,Z, 
for the PLSVO of type number NO_TYPE_OBJECT
(1:POINT, 2:LINE, 3:SURFACE, 4:VOLUME, 5:OBJECT )
the directory number NO_OBJECT
for a temperature TEMPER, known or unknown (not linear case)
must be

DILATA( TEMPS, X, Y, Z, NO_TYPE_OBJET, NO_OBJET, TEMPER ) 

and be programmed with respect to LU grammar
(cf documentation and examples of the debut menu)

All these parameters will be initialized during its call.
These parameters can be used or not, but have to be present
in the definition of DILATATION.
 
EXAMPLE:
deffunc dilatation( t, x, y, z, no_type_objet, material, temper ) ;
if   material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'steel' )
then dilatation=12e-6;
else if material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'copper' )
     then dilatation=16.0e-6 ;
     else dilatation=10.5e-6 ;
     endif;  
endif;
endfunc;

deffunc MaterialRefTemper( t, x, y, z, no_type_objet, material, temper ) ;
if   material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'steel' )
then MaterialRefTemper=20.0;
else if material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'copper' )
     then MaterialRefTemper=18.0;
     else MaterialRefTemper=22.5;
     endif;  
endif;
endfunc;

Remark: the LU function nuobjt( p1, p2 ) gives the
number of the PLSVO of type p1 with the name p2.
